    "causal_summary": "Add hard `responsePolicy` and `citationPolicy` fields to `memory_search` responses so weak retrieval becomes a BINDING claim-authority refusal contract, not advisory text. When `requestQuality.label != \"good\"` AND `recovery.status` indicates degraded, the response carries `responsePolicy.noCanonicalPathClaims:true` and a `safeResponse` string that the model MUST emit instead of inventing details. Also extend `RecoveryAction` vocabulary to include `ask_disambiguation`, `refuse_without_evidence`, and `broaden_or_ask`.",
